1
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:49,930
Give the box to the courier in front of you.

2
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:02,560
The box was thrown away.

3
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:04,080
The tracker inside is useless.

4
00:01:04,080 --> 00:01:06,340
Activate the tracker on the flash drive.

5
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:07,800
Follow from a distance.

6
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:08,860
Don't get spotted.

7
00:01:08,880 --> 00:01:09,400
Okay.

8
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:11,080
Also, put Shao Yu on the phone.

9
00:01:11,160 --> 00:01:11,960
Yes.

10
00:01:24,880 --> 00:01:26,400
Our deal is done, right?

11
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:28,160
No rush.

12
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:29,720
To be honest,

13
00:01:29,880 --> 00:01:32,320
I think you're more capable than my men.

14
00:01:33,240 --> 00:01:34,440
Help me follow them.

15
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:36,780
There might be an unexpected payoff.

16
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:44,600
There is no need for this.

17
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:46,600
Our agreement is already complete.

18
00:02:26,760 --> 00:02:28,040
The tracker's signal is lost.

19
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:29,200
It might have been discovered.

20
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:30,600
Activate the second one.

21
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,490
How did you find this place?

22
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:53,680
You are the famous Lawyer An.

23
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:56,400
It's not hard to find your address.

24
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,360
Weren't you supposed to follow the tracker?

25
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:02,690
What are you doing here?

26
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:04,480
Why would I follow the tracker?

27
00:03:04,480 --> 00:03:06,640
They have already confirmed that the whole lead is fake.

28
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:08,080
What's the point of me following it?

29
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:10,040
Besides, aren't your people following it too?

30
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:11,160
I came to you

31
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:13,490
to see how the second route is developing.

32
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:16,920
Didn't you promise to help me save my daughter?

33
00:03:17,079 --> 00:03:19,079
I have to keep an eye on the progress.

34
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:22,360
But your trick of doing one thing under cover of another

35
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:24,000
is really slick.

36
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:29,160
Although I haven't interacted with you much,

37
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:31,680
I feel like you're not the type to take risks.

38
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:32,880
With this plan,

39
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:35,280
aren't you underestimating the opponent's strength a bit?

40
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:36,340
You guessed right.

41
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:38,940
There are actually two routes tomorrow.

42
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:42,840
For the first one, I need you to do exactly as I just said.

43
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:44,040
As for the second one,

44
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:46,800
first of all, they won't easily believe

45
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,640
that they can get the item so easily.

46
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:51,880
Secondly, I hope to let their own people

47
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:53,360
get their hands on the USB drive.

48
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,680
So your task tomorrow,

49
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:56,440
aside from what I just told you,

50
00:03:56,880 --> 00:03:58,560
is to find a way halfway through

51
00:03:58,560 --> 00:04:00,640
to leak the second route to them

52
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:02,370
and let them get it themselves.

53
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,600
Freshly brewed beauty tea.

54
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:21,800
You're just in time.

55
00:04:22,079 --> 00:04:22,960
Have a taste.

56
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:23,760
Thank you.

57
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,330
It's delicious.

58
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:31,440
Facial masks and beauty tea, Lawyer An,

59
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:33,520
it seems you pay a lot of attention to your image.

60
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:34,450
Well, as a woman,

61
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:38,120
who wouldn't want to keep their youth for a few more years?

62
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:40,640
But with your abilities,

63
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:44,570
I don't think you need to rely on your appearance to score extra points.

64
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:47,400
You know me very well.

65
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:48,360
Just a little.

66
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:50,040
I've learned a bit about you.

67
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:51,680
An Ning,

68
00:04:52,159 --> 00:04:55,360
born in Xiao'an Village, Tazhong County, Tangzhou City.

69
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:56,680
From an ordinary family.

70
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:57,840
To get out of the mountains,

71
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:59,200
you studied hard since childhood

72
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:01,280
and always ranked at the top.

73
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:04,840
Later, you were admitted to Tangzhou University of Political Science and Law as the top student in the county.

74
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:05,320
Then,

75
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:07,760
you went abroad to study at Columbia Law School.

76
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:08,520
After returning to China,

77
00:05:08,520 --> 00:05:11,840
you interned at a top-tier Magic Circle law firm in the country.

78
00:05:11,840 --> 00:05:13,240
In less than three years,

79
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:16,960
you became the youngest partner at this firm.

80
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:21,400
It seems you put a lot of effort into deciding to cooperate with me.

81
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:22,520
Likewise.

82
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:26,680
I've completed everything you assigned to me.

83
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:28,320
How are things progressing on your end?

84
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:29,760
Everything is going smoothly.

85
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:31,020
Just wait for the news.

86
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:34,970
After learning about your resume,

87
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:37,000
I trust you.

88
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:40,320
But seeing you so calm,

89
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:44,560
it seems you're not worried at all that something might go wrong with the USB drive.

90
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:45,800
I guess

91
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:48,640
both of these routes might be fake.

92
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:51,100
The real USB drive is either in Switzerland,

93
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,040
or

94
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:54,040
there's a third route.

95
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:09,040
I'll excuse myself.

96
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:14,840
You're really considerate.

97
00:06:14,840 --> 00:06:18,300
But I think the most important thing in a transaction is trust.

98
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:20,410
I take back what I just said.

99
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:24,040
About the IP address of your home camera you asked me to check,

100
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:24,970
I couldn't do it.

101
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:26,280
Is it that hard?

102
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:27,520
It wasn't supposed to be hard.

103
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:29,840
But an expert built a firewall,

104
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,480
and I can't break through it.

105
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:32,159
An expert?

106
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:33,720
Aren't you an expert?

107
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:34,560
Me?

108
00:06:35,159 --> 00:06:37,360
I'm an expert in Tangzhou at best.

109
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:39,080
That guy is world-class.

110
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:40,480
Let me put it this way.

111
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:42,490
It's like Tyson meeting Ultraman.

112
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:43,600
Will that work?

113
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,240
I'm just letting you know.

114
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,600
I guess finding someone else won't help either.

115
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:47,640
Find another way.

116
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:52,159
No wonder Li Xiangzuo's car hit red lights all the way

117
00:06:52,159 --> 00:06:53,960
and encountered so many situations on the road.

118
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:56,290
It turns out the other party caused it all.

119
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,080
Since I promised you about your daughter's matter,

120
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:04,410
I will definitely do it.

121
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,600
It's time.

122
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,730
I need to take a bath.

123
00:07:07,320 --> 00:07:08,120
Then you...

124
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,240
Thank you for the tea.

125
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:34,180
Help me check Jessica's departure records.

126
00:07:43,159 --> 00:07:44,000
Did you find it?

127
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,260
No departure records.

128
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:48,120
That means she never left.

129
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:55,920
Something came up.

130
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,050
I need to see you now.

131
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:29,760
I got it.

132
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:36,049
What happened to your hand?

133
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:37,760
It's nothing.

134
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:39,289
I accidentally scraped it.

135
00:08:59,080 --> 00:08:59,810
Stop the car.

136
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:52,340
Isn't this Lawyer An's house?

137
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,120
We got played.

138
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:19,120
(Sorry, the subscriber you dialed cannot be connected for the moment.)

139
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:44,560
Everyone.

140
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:46,000
We meet again.

141
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:51,250
How did you find this place?

142
00:11:59,120 --> 00:12:01,040
I clearly checked it.

143
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:05,960
There are two routes they use to transport the flash drive.

144
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:09,080
Every box on each route has a tracker inside.

145
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:11,400
But you only found the first one.

146
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:18,320
Activate the second one.

147
00:12:22,560 --> 00:12:23,120
No need to look.

148
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:24,250
No one followed you.

149
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:26,720
Because I took care of the second one for you.

150
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:27,650
You're welcome.

151
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:37,580
Are you okay, miss?

152
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:40,760
Miss.

153
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,600
Aren't you working with Lawyer An?

154
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:51,000
Why bother swapping the tracker?

155
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,320
My cooperation with that lawyer

156
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:54,400
was just a piece of information I deliberately leaked to you.

157
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:56,200
First, it was to give you a heads-up.

158
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:57,240
They have strength in numbers,

159
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:58,600
and I didn't want you to get hurt.

160
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,320
Second,

161
00:12:59,760 --> 00:13:01,960
it's because I never trust anyone else,

162
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:03,600
only myself.

163
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:06,880
I want to save my daughter with my own hands.

164
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:10,280
So I had to use their plan to find you first.

165
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:12,320
How could you be sure

166
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,800
we would definitely receive the message you sent?

167
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:19,280
Because you have a super hacker here

168
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:20,810
monitoring me at all times.

169
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:23,960
From the very beginning.

170
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:25,360
You've been monitoring

171
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:27,600
and eavesdropping on my every move.

172
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:31,040
You can send messages to Zi via Morse code

173
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:33,000
and hack into the casino's system.

174
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,240
Here is the information you asked for.

175
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:35,880
When I hacked into the casino's surveillance,

176
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:38,000
I found someone else was hacking it too.

177
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,120
You can even obtain data from certain systems

178
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:43,040
and control traffic by changing the lights.

179
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:43,700
Turn right.

180
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:47,660
You are incredibly resourceful.

181
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:50,480
But there's one thing I don't understand.

182
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:52,920
When Hui and I were playing the last round,

183
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:54,800
I let Zi play at the last minute.

184
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:56,400
And the cards were dealt manually.

185
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:57,880
How did you make her win?

186
00:13:58,040 --> 00:14:00,240
Because we bribed the dealer in advance

187
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:03,080
to cooperate with me throughout the game.

188
00:14:03,560 --> 00:14:06,320
Even if you changed the rules temporarily,

189
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:08,480
she could use subtle expressions

190
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:09,740
to send messages to me.

191
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:38,280
Then how did you know

192
00:14:38,280 --> 00:14:39,320
I hadn't left?

193
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:40,640
I didn't know at first.

194
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:43,280
I only knew that you two were in contact.

195
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:46,960
He replied to my message.

196
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:50,130
I just roughly memorized that number.

197
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:52,600
If I hadn't been injured while escorting Jessica,

198
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:56,120
and she hadn't used a hidden phone to order food and buy medicine for me,

199
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:57,560
I wouldn't have found out.

200
00:14:57,560 --> 00:14:59,760
It turns out Jessica's phone number ending

201
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:00,760
and your friend's

202
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:02,120
are exactly the same.

203
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:07,770
Is it the one ending in 2350?

204
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:12,120
When I looked at your phone in the park,

205
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:14,200
I just wanted to confirm my guess.

206
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:16,730
But I accidentally saw your chat history.

207
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:19,360
Only then did I know Jessica hadn't left at all.

208
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:20,440
Give me your phone.

209
00:15:28,520 --> 00:15:29,320
Now,

210
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:33,450
give my daughter back to me.

211
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,560
If I said

212
00:15:40,560 --> 00:15:42,420
we really don't know where she is,

213
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:44,080
would you believe it?

214
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,600
Are you going to say you were instructed by someone else,

215
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:48,730
and there's someone else behind this?

216
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:14,920
Hello, Officer Shao.

217
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:17,640
Did you get your flash drive?

218
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:20,330
The countdown hasn't stopped, has it?

219
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:25,680
It's right here.

220
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:36,600
Is it real?

221
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:44,320
Even if you cooperate with that lawyer,

222
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:46,560
she wouldn't be so kind as to give you the real one.

223
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:47,400
Of course not.

224
00:16:48,560 --> 00:16:50,080
I saw from the very beginning

225
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:53,160
that the flash drives transported on both routes were fake.

226
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:54,040
All the plans

227
00:16:54,040 --> 00:16:55,800
were aimed at luring you out.

228
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:58,640
That lawyer said the flash drive was in Switzerland,

229
00:16:58,640 --> 00:17:00,120
which was just a cover.

230
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:02,160
How could she keep something so important in Switzerland?

231
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:04,119
She must have kept it within her sight.

232
00:17:04,119 --> 00:17:05,520
I just didn't know where.

233
00:17:06,319 --> 00:17:08,000
The electronic key and Jessica

234
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:10,200
are the two keys to open the flash drive.

235
00:17:10,319 --> 00:17:12,400
But the electronic key is carried by her boss.

236
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,400
I couldn't get it.

237
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:14,599
So,

238
00:17:14,599 --> 00:17:17,280
I could only use the other one.

239
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:23,800
It's actually quite simple.

240
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:25,760
I just leaked the news that Jessica is still in the country

241
00:17:25,760 --> 00:17:27,160
to that lawyer.

242
00:17:27,160 --> 00:17:30,000
Then she had to hurry and destroy the real flash drive backup.

243
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,920
I'm a master in Tangzhou at best,

244
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:33,720
but the opponent is world-class.

245
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:36,880
No wonder Li Xiangzuo's car hit red lights all the way.

246
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:39,920
There is no departure information.

247
00:17:40,520 --> 00:17:42,040
That means she didn't leave at all.

248
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:42,880
Something came up.

249
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:44,010
I need to see you now.

250
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:54,760
She didn't go anywhere else on the way,

251
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:56,320
nor did she carry anything.

252
00:17:56,760 --> 00:17:59,320
So I guess the flash drive must be on her.

253
00:17:59,440 --> 00:17:59,880
I figured it out.

254
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:02,240
I previously sent someone to gather a lot of information on her.

255
00:18:02,240 --> 00:18:03,520
She is very similar to Jessica.

256
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:04,320
She dresses fashionably,

257
00:18:04,320 --> 00:18:05,320
wears exquisite makeup,

258
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:07,050
and cares a lot about her image.

259
00:18:07,080 --> 00:18:08,760
In all the pictures I saw of her,

260
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:10,480
she would choose different jewelry

261
00:18:10,480 --> 00:18:12,080
to match different outfits.

262
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:14,280
But the pendant on her chest

263
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:15,520
is the only thing she never changed.

264
00:18:15,520 --> 00:18:17,040
So I figure

265
00:18:17,320 --> 00:18:18,720
the thing is right there.
